<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 08 at 12:25PM CST  by NWS Lake Charles</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT WESTERN RAPIDES AND EASTERN
VERNON PARISHES THROUGH 115 PM CST...
At 1225 PM CST, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Pitkin, moving northeast at 45 mph.
HAZARD...Penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to vegetation and outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Alexandria, Boyce, Hineston, Lena, Alexandria International Airport,
Pitkin, Lacamp, Timber Trails, Fullerton, Hutton, Clifton, Flatwoods,
Otis, Elmer, Leander, Sieper, Gardner, Cravens, Calcasieu, and
Simpson.
This includes Interstate 49 between mile markers 91 and 109.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
